{"claim_id": "claim_011", "text": "The ratio of ChIP to control reads in the example MACS3 analysis is approximately 0.99858.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "resulting in a ratio of\napproximately 0.99858", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [22377, 22422], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_012", "text": "The predictd subcommand in MACS3 determined a fragment length of 254 base pairs for the CTCF ChIP sample.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "3 `callpeak`, use\n`-m 5 50`. Of course, you can adjust these parameters as needed. The\noutput from `predictd` will provide the fragment length `d`, which in\nthis example is `254`.", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [23722, 23901], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3", "callpeak_subcommand", "predictd_subcommand", "callpeak_pipeline_architecture"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_016", "text": "In the example MACS3 analysis, the normalization factor for the 1kb background is 0.254, calculated as d/slocal (254/1000).", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "which is 254/1000 = 0.254 in our\nexample. To do this, apply the `bdgopt` subcommand:\n\n```\n$ macs3", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [28015, 28112], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3", "bdgopt_subcommand"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_017", "text": "In the example MACS3 analysis, the normalization factor for the 10kb background is 0.0254, calculated as d/llocal (254/10000).", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "The appropriate multiplier is `d/llocal`, or 0.0254 in\nour example:\n\n```\n$ macs3 bdgopt -i 10", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [28834, 28927], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3", "bdgopt_subcommand"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_018", "text": "In the example MACS3 analysis, the whole genome background is calculated as 0.0188023, derived from 199,867 reads × 254 bp / 2,700,000,000 bp.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "199867 * 254 / 2700000000 ≈ 0.0188023", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [6471, 6507], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_019", "text": "In the example MACS3 analysis, the control bias is scaled down by a factor of 0.99858 to match the ChIP sequencing depth.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "the control bias needs to be scaled down using the ratio between ChIP\nand control, which is 199,583/199,867 = 0.99858", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_epigenomics/coll_macs/synthesized_package", "source_section": "methods", "page": null, "char_span": [30837, 30954], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": null, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["MACS3"]}
